The paper deals with the problem of recovering a low-rank matrix from incomplete and possibly noisy linear measurements, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science and engineering. The paper uses probabilistic modeling and convex optimization to derive recovery results, which are techniques commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and numerical analysis (cs.NA), as well as quantum physics (cs.SI). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
